# ScriStaller

A Bash script to easily install and manage your own scripts on your system.

## Features
- Install scripts to a central location (e.g., /usr/local/bin/)
- Rename scripts for easy command-line access
- Update or replace existing scripts

## Usage
```bash
./ScriStaller <script> <commandName>
```

- `<script>`: Path to the script you want to install
- `<commandName>`: Name for the installed script

### Example
```bash
./ScriStaller my_script.sh my_command
```

## Tips
- To uninstall, run ScriStaller again with the same script but omit the command name
- Ensure you have permissions to write to /usr/local/bin/

